OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe return of Loose Women sees
OL,4,Clunchtime news move back to 1.30pm
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe main weekday bulletins should be at
OL,7,Ffixed times.
OL,9,FOf course, ITV moves News at Ten
OL,10,Fregularly ` it has not been at 10pm
OL,11,Fsince before Easter. But at least when
OL,12,FNews at Ten is late it is usually
OL,13,Fbecause of a programme which is
OL,14,Fespecially popular or significant.
OL,16,FGiven the way the Lunchtime News is
OL,17,Ftreated, it is hardly surprising the
OL,18,FBBC News at One outrates it three times
OL,19,Fover.
OL,23,EPub: 17-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
